Natural language: List all films.
Show all film titles with their release year.
generated_SPARQL:
PREFIX ex: <http://example.org/movies/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

SELECT ?title ?year
WHERE {
  ?film rdf:type ex:Film .
  ?film ex:title ?title .
  ?film ex:year ?year .
}
the correct sparql: SELECT ?title ?year WHERE { ?film a ex:Film ; ex:title ?title ; ex:year ?year . }

PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

  ?director ex:name "Christopher Nolan" .

}

Natural language: Which films were released after 2010?

PREFIX ex: <http://example.org/movies/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

SELECT ?title
WHERE {
  ?film rdf:type ex:Film .
  ?film ex:year ?year .

Natural language: Which films have a rating higher than 8.5?

PREFIX ex: <http://example.org/movies/>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>

SELECT ?title
WHERE {
  ?film a ex:Film .
  ?film ex:title ?title .
  ?film ex:rating ?rating .

}

Natural language: List all science fiction films.
generated_SPARQL:
PREFIX ex: <http://example.org/movies/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

SELECT ?title
WHERE {
  ?film rdf:type ex:Film .
  ?film ex:hasGenre ex:Science_Fiction .
  ?film ex:title ?title .
}

Natural language: Which films belong to more than one genre?
the correct sparql:
SELECT ?title (COUNT(?genre) AS ?nbGenres)
        WHERE { ?film ex:title ?title ; ex:hasGenre ?genre . }
        GROUP BY ?title
        HAVING(COUNT(?genre) > 1)

Natural language: Which actors have appeared in more than one film?
generated_SPARQL:
PREFIX ex: <http://example.org/movies/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT ?actorName
WHERE {
  ?film ex:actor ?actor .
  ?actor ex:name ?actorName .
}
GROUP BY ?actorName
HAVING (COUNT(?film) > 1)
the correct sparql:
SELECT ?actor (COUNT(?film) AS ?count)
        WHERE { ?film ex:actor ?actor . }
        GROUP BY ?actor
        HAVING(COUNT(?film) > 1)

Natural language: How many films are in the database?
List films released between 2000 and 2015.
generated_SPARQL:
PREFIX ex: <http://example.org/movies/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

SELECT ?film ?title
WHERE {
  ?film a ex:Film .
  ?film ex:title ?title .
  ?film ex:year ?year .
  FILTER (?year >= 2000 && ?year <= 2015)
}

Natural language: Which films starring Leonardo DiCaprio were released after 2000?
generated_SPARQL:
PREFIX ex: <http://example.org/movies/>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>

SELECT ?title
WHERE {
  ?film ex:actor ?actor .
  ?actor ex:name "Leonardo DiCaprio" .
  ?film ex:year ?year .
  ?film ex:title ?title .
  FILTER (?year > 2000)
}
the correct sparql: SELECT ?title WHERE { ?film ex:title ?title ; ex:actor ex:Leonardo_DiCaprio ; ex:year ?year . FILTER(?year > 2000) }

Natural language: Which Christopher Nolan films have a rating above 8.7?
the correct sparql: SELECT ?title WHERE { ?film ex:title ?title ; ex:director ex:Christopher_Nolan ; ex:rating ?rating . FILTER(?rating > 8.7) }

Natural language: What is the average release year of all films?
Which films were produced by someone different from the director?
the correct sparql: SELECT ?title WHERE { ?film ex:title ?title ; ex:director ?d ; ex:producer ?p . FILTER(?d != ?p) }

Natural language: What are the most common film genres?
generated_SPARQL:
PREFIX ex: <http://example.org/movies/>
SELECT ?genre (COUNT(?film) AS ?filmCount)
WHERE {
  ?film ex:hasGenre ?genre .
}
GROUP BY ?genre
ORDER BY DESC(?filmCount)
the correct sparql: SELECT ?genre (COUNT(?film) AS ?count) WHERE { ?film ex:hasGenre ?genre . } GROUP BY ?genre ORDER BY DESC(?count)
